Kiwi is a PHP command line application that maps data from KE Software's EMu
collection management system into the Apache Solr search server.

Kiwi is written for PHP 5.2.  It requires that your PHP server support process controls:

http://www.php.net/pcntl

Although not required, the Tidy extension is recommended for improved debugging:

http://www.php.net/tidy

Kiwi is released under the GNU General Public License, version 2 and later. See
the included LICENSE.txt file for more information.

Development of Kiwi is sponsored by the Field Museum of Natural History (http://fieldmuseum.org/) in Chicago, USA.

Kiwi includes the following 3rd party libraries:

---QueryPath: http://www.querypath.org/

QueryPath is an XML parsing library for PHP.  Think of it as jQuery for PHP. It
is licensed under the LGPL.  See QueryPath/LGPL-2.1.txt for more information.

---SolrPhpClient: http://code.google.com/p/solr-php-client/

SolrPhpClient is a PHP library for interfacing with an Apache Solr search server.
It is licensed under the New BSD License.  See SolrPhpClient/COPYING for more
information.

---IMu: http://www.kesoftware.com/

IMu is part of KE Software's Electronic Museum (EMu) collection management system.
It provides web-based access to an EMu server. Kiwi (named in EMu's honor)
includes the PHP connector library included with IMu under a BSD-style license.
See emu/LICENSE.txt for more information.
